1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,775
In this episode, we'll look at governance and smart contract auctions.

2
00:00:04,725 --> 00:00:09,837
The Voting page lets you participate in community governance on the Qubic network.

3
00:00:09,837 --> 00:00:13,375
Browse active proposals to see what's being voted on.

4
00:00:13,375 --> 00:00:17,150
The Browse tab lists all current and past proposals.

5
00:00:17,150 --> 00:00:22,075
Cast your vote on the Vote tab by selecting a proposal and choosing your option.

6
00:00:22,075 --> 00:00:27,387
View results with progress bars on the Results tab — see how the community is leaning.

7
00:00:27,387 --> 00:00:30,825
You can also create a new poll from the Create tab.

8
00:00:30,825 --> 00:00:35,412
Set a question, define the options, and submit it to the network.

9
00:00:35,412 --> 00:00:38,562
Now let's look at Smart Contract Auctions.

10
00:00:38,562 --> 00:00:43,475
SC Auctions shows available smart contract slots on the Qubic network.

11
00:00:43,475 --> 00:00:48,587
The Browse tab lists active auctions with their current bid status and time remaining.

12
00:00:48,587 --> 00:00:52,787
The Status tab lets you check the status of a specific auction.

13
00:00:52,787 --> 00:00:57,287
And the Bid tab lets you place bids to secure a smart contract slot.

14
00:00:57,287 --> 00:01:01,337
Enter the auction details and your bid amount, then submit.

15
00:01:01,337 --> 00:01:09,637
These governance features give you a direct voice in the Qubic ecosystem — from voting on proposals to securing smart contract capacity.

